snippet.textDisplay:
- Decree a norm of obligatory character so that every person who comes from travel and enters the country is forced to wear the mask for a month, this could reduce the spread of the virus a little (in case of entering a citizen with the virus).
We must remember the cases of Korea and Italy, countries that are struggling to know who was the first "super contagious patient", it would have been better to be fighting to want to know who was the "less contagious" patient if he had been forced by a law to wear a mask.
So that people who have come on a trip and are forced to wear masks, and so that they do not feel "discriminated against", regulate that all public officials (at airports, police, etc.) begin using masks (prevent is better than sorry) in this way travelers will feel that their use is general and non-discriminatory.
- During this year, to recommend to people to greet each other by shaking hands, only one gesture would suffice.
- Teach people to make masks at home, with double lining, it is not difficult to manufacture.
- In quarantine periods, oblige any citizen who has a simple cough to stay at home.
- Prepare containers (with prepared rooms) to isolate patients outside the city; ; they are cheaper and fast manufacturing than being doing large hospitals
- Instruct citizens that the majority of those killed by Coronavirus are people with low immune defenses, so feed well.
